column4: Ok.  one more time.  can anyone help me with my network printer?
I'm trying to get this (ubuntu) box to talk to a printer on a little print server thingie
(it attaches to the parallel port of the printer)
my windows box can see & print from that fine
for the windows box, it's an SMB printer
but I don't know how to make it run for this one
use samba to set it up on your local machine
I don't know what I"m doing wrong
well what have you done so far
tried to add it as a network printer...
for host, I put whatever I see on the "network" tab in nautilus
I set it to P1, since that's what worked on the other box
and I set it to print a test page
the test page never comes out.  it's showing a timeout
use lpr from the command line to print directly to it
